                  }
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                " Sample foils, exp. method, error propagation given"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "institute": "2JPNKTO"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Kyoto University Reactor (KUR) with the",
                " heavy-water neutron facility.",
                "Fission converters were mounted in cubic concrete-",
                " shielded room, 2.4 m from the reactor core.",
                "The space in between was occupied by a large heavy",
                " water tank and a Bi window."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Thermal neutrons on a large fission plate (31.3 cm in",
                " diameter and 1.1 cm thick), made of 90% 235U enriched",
                " UO2-Al cermet plate (27 cm diameter) clad by Al.",
                "Total amount of uranium about 1.1 kg."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The deviation of the spectrum calculated by MCNP from",
                " the Watt spectrum is small above 1.5 MeV, but",
                " gradually increases at decreasing energy.",
                "According to the initial calibration, when the fission",
                " plate was irradiated by average thermal neutron flux",
                " density 5.8E+8 n/cm2/s at power level 5 MW, fast",
                " neutron flux density at the center of fission plate",
                " and the fission power of the plate were",
                " 1.8E+9 n/cm2/sec and 0.53 W, respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The samples were attached at the center on the back",
                " side of the fission converter plate."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Foils of different isotopes were activated",
                " using large fission plate converter fields."
              ]
            }
          ],
